cs.MM, cs.NI, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.CR

The paper discusses HTTP Adaptive Streaming, which is related to multimedia delivery and network conditions. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also discusses bitrate adaptation algorithms, which involve network capacity utilization and throughput-based and buffer-based adaptation mechanisms, indicating a possible fit with cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The use of scalable video coding and video quality improvement suggests a possible fit with cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses filling levels of playback buffers, which may relate to information theory and compression, indicating a possible fit with cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper may also relate to cryptography and security, which could suggest a possible fit with cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
